    "description": "Neuland Laboratories Holdings Services has an exciting opening for a Surgeon at our Meerut office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Neuland Laboratories Holdings Services:\nNeuland Laboratories Holdings Services is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Respond to medical emergencies and provide immediate care\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Post Graduate Diploma in relevant field\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in NABH Standards\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in ICU Management\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Flexible working hours\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Meerut, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Neuland Laboratories Holdings Services!",
